  </div>


<p><span><span><a href="https://brill.com/view/title/60446"><em><span><span>Matsuri and Religion: Complexity, Continuity, and Creativity in Japanese Festivals</span></span></em>.</a> Leiden: Brill, 2021. Co-Edited with Elisabetta Porcu.&nbsp; </span></span></p>
<a href="https://brill.com/view/title/60446">
<div class="media media--type-sf-image-media-type media--view-mode-sf-small">
  
          <img loading="lazy" src="/sites/g/files/dgvnsk4911/files/styles/sf_small_width/public/media/images/cover%20image.jpg?itok=nWlu4ZjF" width="200" height="305" alt="cover image Matsuri and Religion" class="image-style-sf-small-width">




  </div>
</a>

<p><a href="https://brill.com/view/journals/jrj/9/1-3/jrj.9.issue-1-3.xml"><em><span><span>Matsuri and Religion in Japan</span></span></em></a><span><span>; Special Triple Issue of <em>Journal of Religion in Japan </em>vol. 9, issues 1-3, 2020. Co-edited with Elisabetta Porcu.</span></span><a href="https://brill.com/view/journals/jrj/9/1-3/jrj.9.issue-1-3.xml"> </a></p>

<p><a href="https://www.degruyter.com/view/journals/fabl/58/1-2/fabl.58.issue-1-2.xml"><em>We are all Survivors: Verbal, Ritual and Material Ways of Narrating Disaster and Recovery</em></a>; Special Issue of&nbsp;<em>Fabula: Journal of Folktale Studies</em>&nbsp;58, issues 1-2, 2017. Co-Edited with Carl Lindahl.</p>

<p><a href="https://upcolorado.com/utah-state-university-press/item/2751-the-folkloresque"><em>The Folkloresque: Reframing Folklore in a Popular Culture World</em></a>. Co-Edited with Jeffrey A. Tolbert. Logan: Utah State University Press, 2016. Co-Edited with Jeffrey Tolbert.</p>

<p><img alt="Folkloresque cover" data-entity-type="file" data-entity-uuid="5562f0ee-d417-4dbf-8596-a0f18db50b07" height="202" src="/sites/g/files/dgvnsk4911/files/inline-images/Foster%20Folkloresque%20cover.jpg" width="134"></p>

<p><a href="https://iupress.org/9780253019400/unesco-on-the-ground/"><em>UNESCO on the Ground: Local Perspectives on Intangible Cultural Heritage</em></a>. Co-Edited with Lisa Gilman. Bloomington: Indiana University Press, 2015. Co-Edited with Lisa Gilman.</p>

